WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:02.697
And it was so sickening what I was watching happening.

00:00:02.697 --> 00:00:06.560
But the Lord said, "This is closer than you realize.

00:00:06.560 --> 00:00:10.030
" And then you get to step two, Andrew, which is: "I'd like my child to be really smart.

00:00:10.030 --> 00:00:11.990
" Step three: "I'd like my child to be really tall.

00:00:11.990 --> 00:00:18.960
" And before you know it, we're well on the way to what could be described as eugenics or playing God.

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:24.783
And they grew the baby to what you had specifically wanted—hair color, eye color.

00:00:25.546 --> 00:00:29.101
You know, like you go to the mall and Build-a-Bear; it was build-a-baby.

00:00:29.359 --> 00:00:35.988
And they could have the gender they wanted, the hair color, the structure of the body; everything was in design.

00:00:36.399 --> 00:00:41.920
If it wasn't right, they aborted it because it wasn't what they had ordered.

00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:44.480
I'm afraid, Andrew, that I don't see any bright lines.

00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:47.920
Once you go down this path, there won't be any bright lines.

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:52.239
And then once we genetically modify everybody into perfection, we'll all be exactly the same.

00:00:52.239 --> 00:00:54.599
It's the same spirit that was behind Hitler.

00:00:54.599 --> 00:00:57.479
The same thinking that Hitler had—it's sickening.

00:00:57.479 --> 00:00:59.167
This should be illegal.

00:00:59.167 --> 00:01:03.885
We're all fearfully and wonderfully made by the Father.

00:01:03.885 --> 00:01:06.671
The Lord showed me this and it was very disturbing.

00:01:06.671 --> 00:01:16.551
He showed me surrogate mothers—mothers that did not want to carry a baby but would pay somebody else to do it.

00:01:16.551 --> 00:01:21.383
That would become something that people don't do anymore.

00:01:21.383 --> 00:01:30.080
I saw lab-tube babies that would be created with AI technology.

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:37.306
You take the egg and the seed—the sperm—and you make a baby in a lab-tube.

00:01:37.306 --> 00:01:40.560
They would grow it in an incubator.

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:47.076
It was like a real womb, a surrogate that didn't have to be human.

00:01:47.076 --> 00:01:52.192
It was a tube in a lab; it wasn't that big.

00:01:57.812 --> 00:02:02.240
And instead of having a surrogate woman, it was a surrogate tube.

00:02:02.240 --> 00:02:13.209
And they grew the baby to what you had specifically wanted: hair color, eye color, like a Build-a-Bear.

00:02:15.659 --> 00:02:15.879
It was build-a-baby.

00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:27.223
And they could have the gender they wanted, the hair color, the structure of the body; everything was in design.

00:02:27.223 --> 00:02:39.070
And if it wasn't right, they aborted it because it wasn't what they had ordered, like an AI order.

00:02:40.978 --> 00:02:43.040
This is what we want at the lab.

00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:52.120
And they created it with genetic modification of human life in a tube.

00:02:52.120 --> 00:02:54.799
And in certain countries, they made it legal.

00:02:54.799 --> 00:03:03.360
And you did not have to have a surrogate woman anymore to carry your baby for you because the celebrities—these people were into their looks.

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:14.446
Big-money people were into their looks, and they didn't want to pay for a surrogate because you'd have to worry about what they're eating, what they're drinking, or who they are, or if they're weird.

00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:19.599
They said, "Well, we'll just let the lab do it.

00:03:19.599 --> 00:03:26.208
" They paid mega money for what they specifically wanted for a build-a-child.

00:03:27.744 --> 00:03:29.400
And it was very disturbing.

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:32.419
So, I saw the child be born.

00:03:32.419 --> 00:03:40.599
It was ready to hatch out of this womb thing with bubbles bubbling all around it, keeping the baby alive.

00:03:40.599 --> 00:03:52.219
It was AI technology beyond anything you can comprehend, taking the egg from the woman and the seed from the man and creating a child with your DNA.

00:03:53.223 --> 00:04:02.902
But there was no—and this is what I thought was interesting—I saw the baby and there was no connection.

00:04:12.939 --> 00:04:28.560
What I could see in the face was there was no real connection like when a mother carries a child normally; there's a connection and a bond that is created with the human that is only done by God.

00:04:40.650 --> 00:04:40.860
And when this is not made there, it was almost like looking at a child with autism where the lights are on, but no one's home.

00:04:40.860 --> 00:04:45.440
I don't mean that disrespectfully, but I'm trying to describe it.

00:04:48.030 --> 00:04:55.830
This is what these children looked like in their eyes; there was just this disconnect.

00:04:55.840 --> 00:04:58.120
But I saw this thing coming.

00:04:58.120 --> 00:05:00.800
Now, I don't know how this would happen.

00:05:01.640 --> 00:05:03.199
It seems so far out there.

00:05:03.199 --> 00:05:13.310
But the Lord told me to warn you that this is coming: lab-grown children, lab-grown life.

00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:21.669
Then I saw them in labs, and they were doing genetic code in Japan and China and some other places.

00:05:21.669 --> 00:05:28.857
I don't know if the United States would come right out and do this very fast, but I saw foreign countries have no restraints.

00:05:31.620 --> 00:05:36.000
I saw lab-grown babies again.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:44.376
And they were making something that looked like a superhuman—what they thought was a perfect child.

00:05:53.690 --> 00:06:00.560
They were trying to be like Hitler with ethnic cleansing.

00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:12.823
This is what they will eliminate by making a superhuman race without any kind of flaws through an artificial womb.

00:06:15.840 --> 00:06:23.029
An artificial womb that looked the size of a toilet bowl.

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:31.199
As it was growing and developing, if it wasn't what they wanted, they just aborted it—build-a-baby.

00:06:34.016 --> 00:06:46.320
And I said that yesterday; I was hearing a celebrity and many of you got her name right, which I thought was interesting.

00:06:55.739 --> 00:07:03.549
My son told me who you all were saying in the chat and there were so many people saying the exact same person.

00:07:03.959 --> 00:07:14.639
I heard her talking and I will never say it on here, and I encourage you all not to either, but they were saying it right.

00:07:14.811 --> 00:07:29.489
I heard the celebrity talking and they were saying this is convenient so as not to put stress on the woman's body because it's too much for their organs.

00:07:31.230 --> 00:07:41.039
This is more convenient so that we can multiply our bloodlines to make sure that name is sustained in the earth.

00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:50.040
You want to make sure you have strong men to take on that name.

00:07:58.709 --> 00:08:03.470
Some names mean more than others in their opinion.

00:08:03.960 --> 00:08:14.1000
So you raise up a bunch of these celebrity names and males to take on that name of that celebrity or royalty.

00:08:18.628 --> 00:08:25.090
But in a superhuman, beautiful eyes—this is guaranteed, ma'am.

00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:30.929
You put this in there and they're never going to have cancer; we'll be able to take that genetic out of there.

00:08:30.929 --> 00:08:35.976
And it was so sickening what I was watching happening.

00:08:35.976 --> 00:08:40.000
But the Lord said, "This is closer than you realize.

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:48.720
" When I was in there looking at the vision, I heard the voice of the Lord and he said, "This is closer than you realize.

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:57.580
" And then I saw babies in labs in amniotic fluid with bubbling and a light behind it.

00:08:57.580 --> 00:09:03.954
It looked like a hot light keeping this baby warm, like something in a sci-fi movie.

00:09:10.731 --> 00:09:13.897
What you could see wasn't fully developed yet.

00:09:14.331 --> 00:09:19.799
I could see the nose and the head and how it separates from the egg and the sperm.

00:09:22.110 --> 00:09:23.510
Life without a mother.

00:09:23.510 --> 00:09:26.240
And I saw they were doing it; it was successful.

00:09:26.240 --> 00:09:36.800
It was alive in a cylinder tube, suspended in this amniotic fluid stuff and real-life bubbles that were moving around this human life.

00:09:46.648 --> 00:09:52.080
I could see the fluids and it looked like the amniotic fluid had a yellow tint.

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:58.126
